- Adjectives: emit the SINGLE dictionary base form only (e.g. "stor" not "stor, stora"). Never pair an adjective with its inflected form — Swedish does NOT inflect adjectives by gender in the dictionary entry.
- "translation" field for NOUN entries: mirror the source's article category into German:
  • DEF source ("hunden") → "der Hund" (German def).
  • INDEF source ("en hund") → "ein Hund" (German indef).
  • BARE source → "ein Hund" (German indef — bare mirrors to indef).
- List every exact word form from the source text (inflected forms, plurals, conjugations) in "source_forms".

"type" must be one of: "noun", "verb", "adjective", "phrase", "other".
Pick the type that matches each extracted word — DO NOT label every entry "noun". Verbs are infinitives (e.g. "att springa"); phrases are multi-word fixed expressions.

